                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus>
                    Hymn to Mary, “We Send Praise to Mary, Holder of the Divine,” <foreign xml:lang="gez"> ስብሐተ ለማርያም ንፈኑ ይእቲ ለመለኮት ክዳኑ</foreign>, with musical notation
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                    Excerpt from the <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3851Hassab">We have written a
                                                  computus that we will remember in order not to
                                                  congregate with apostates...</title> on moveable feasts, in Amharic
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto) #iiv(erso)" facs="002 003">Folss. iir(ecto), iiv(erso), </locus>
                    Excerpt from a Hymn book, with musical notation. Within the text there is a note of ownership by Abba Čäre (<locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">iir(ecto), </locus>), corrected to Qäs Čäbäre (<locus target="#3r" facs="005">3r</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    Excerpt from the Conclusion of the Anaphora of Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅዳሴ ማርያም</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r #3v #4r #5r #6r #6v" facs="004 006 007 008 009">Fols. 1v, 2r, 3v, 4r, 5r, 6r, 6v</locus>: Excerpt from the <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3851Hassab">We have written a
                                                  computus that we will remember in order not to
                                                  congregate with apostates...</title>, in Amharic.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="am">ከጅጉ በጥቂቱ የባሕረ አሳብ ነገር እንናገራለን መጥቅ አስራራትን አአይነካም (sic)<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="005">Fol. 2v</locus>
                    Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6024IntroMM">Introductory text
                                                  and hymn to the Miracles of Mary</title>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወኢይምሰሎ ለኵሉ ቀሊለ ሰሚዓ ተአምሪሃ ለማርያም እስመ ዓቢይ ወክቡር ውእቱ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#3r" facs="005"> f. 3r, top</locus>
                    Excerpt from Prayers by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#3r" facs="005"> f. 3r, bottom</locus>
                    Excerpt from a hymn book
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <locus target="#4r" facs="006"> f. 4r, lines 5ff</locus>
                      Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2765RepCh49">Malkǝʾ-hymn (Salām)
                                                  to Phanuel</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#4v" facs="007">Fol. 4v</locus>
                    Prayer of Benediction, “Grace of the Father,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋ ዘአብ</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋ ዘአብ ኂሩት ዘወልድ ሱታፌ (ዘመንፈስ ቅዱስ) እግዚአብሔር የሀቦ ለብፁ ወቅዱስ ሊቀ ጳጳስነ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a11">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#33v" facs="036">Fol. 33v</locus>
                    Medical prescription for impotence.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅንቡርስ አድርቆ እፅፋርስ መርዝ ተቀጽላ ይህን አንድ ላይ ደቁሶ በጣዝማ ማር ለውሶ ቅባ ሙር ጥህን ተገናኝ።</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a12">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#33v #34r" facs="036">Fols. 33v, 34r</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> Prayer for attraction of women, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ መስተፋቅር</foreign>. Some words in this text are Arabic words written in Gǝ‘ǝz characters.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ መስተፋቅር አላሁማ ፫ ጊዜ ረበዋን ኢጅማን በስቡጻ ሰሀባ ወአቅባ ወአቁም አማውተ<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a13">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#34r #34v #35r #35v" facs="036 037 038">Fols. 34r, 34v, 35r, 35v</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> Prayer against the evil eye, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ ዓይነ ወርቅ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ ንድራ</foreign>, including Prayer against the witch at the Sea of Galilee.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት በእንተ ዓይነ ወርቅ ጸሎተ ንድራ እግዚእነ ኢየሱስ ክርስቶ(ስ) ውስተ ባሕረ ጥብርያዶስ<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a14">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#35v #36r #36v" facs="038 039">Fols. 35v, 36r, 36v</locus>
                    Excerpt from a Hymn to the Trinity, “The Trinity Renders People Silent and Fills with Wonder,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥላሴ ትትረመም ወትትነከር እስመ</foreign>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥላሴ ትትረመም ወትትነከር እስመ በስላሴ ትሄሉ ሰማያት ወምድር<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a15">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#63r" facs="065">Fol. 63r</locus>
                    List of Titles of Hymns
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a16">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#63v #64r" facs="066">Fols. 63v, 64r</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6375HeavenOpen">Rǝḫwa samāy</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a17">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#64r #64v" facs="066 067">Fols. 64r, 64v</locus>
                    Excerpt from Book of Hymns
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a18">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#64v" facs="067">Fol. 64v</locus>
                    Hymn to Mary: “Pray for Us, Mary, to Your Son,” <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአሊ ለነ ማርያም ወልድኪ</foreign>, with musical notation.
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰአሊ ለነ ማርያም ወልድኪ ይምሐረነ ወይሠሃለነ ኃበ ኄር መደኃኒነ: (sic)<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#5v" facs="008">Fol. 5v</locus>
                    pen trial
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#16 #29 #35" facs="018 031 037">Fols. 16, 29, 35</locus>
                      white string is sewn into the top edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12v #15v" facs="015 018">folss. 12v, 15v, </locus>);
                      words of text are written in the upper margin in purple ink with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#41v" facs="044"> f. 41v, col. 2, line 3</locus><locus target="#46r" facs="048"> f. 46r, col. 1, line 6</locus>), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used in yellow ink (<locus target="#50r" facs="052"> f. 50r, col. 1, line 8</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#7v" facs="010">7v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
